Hysteria/Tavatron

Hysteria:

The doors buckled and groaned with the blast. The horn missiles had 
penetrated the door, and due to it's weakened moleculer structure had 
created a rather good sized hole considering the density of the door:

CF COMP: Penetration, main entrance doors.

Hysteria dropped what she was doing and brought up a hazy image of the 
blasted entry way on the console screen:

"Seal the door."

CF COMP: Unable to comply. Seal has been penetrated.

Hysteria banged a fist against the console. So much for the lockdown. It was 
still in effect everywhere else, but the door HAD been penetrated. Well, the 
shield was still active, though a little shaky it should hold. Plus the 
ceasefire prevented the Alliance from blasting at the shields.

Tavatron:

Tavatron growled under her breath as she fought every primal instinct she 
had to jump on Lion and rip him limb from limb. The waiting had made her 
anxious and extremely tempermental. It was bad enough she couldn't shoot 
anything, but to merely stand by while her commander was insulted was 
seriously pushing it. Something had better happen, and soon.
